<div class="stars-container">
  <div id="stars"></div>
  <div id="stars2"></div>
  <div id="stars3"></div>

  <div class="title-container" >
    <div class="title">
      <h2>Scroll down to start space journey</h2>
      <p>Interactive CV</p>
        <%= image_tag "spaceship.png", id:"spaceship" %>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="planets" data-aos="fade-left"
     data-aos-anchor="#trigger-left"
 >
    <%= image_tag "jupiter.png", id:"jupiter" %>
  </div>

  <div class="planets" data-aos="fade-right"
     data-aos-anchor="#trigger-right">
    <%= image_tag "moon.png", id:"moon" %>
  </div>

  <div class="planets" data-aos="fade-left"
     data-aos-anchor="#trigger-earth">
    <%= image_tag "planet-earth.png", id:"earth" %>
  </div>

  <div class="item"></div>
  <div class="item"></div>
  <div class="item" id="trigger-left"></div>
  <div class="item" id="trigger-right"></div>
  <div class="item" id="trigger-earth"></div>
  <div class="item" id="first"></div>


  <div class="text" data-aos="zoom-out"
       data-aos-anchor="#trigger-left"
       data-aos-delay="200" id="first-text">
    <p>Hi there!</p>
    <p>My name is Cindy Xie.</p>
    <p>I am originally from New York City, where I lived until summer 2017.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="text" data-aos="zoom-out"
    data-aos-anchor="#trigger-right"
    data-aos-delay="200" id="second-text">
    <p>I have always had an interest in the web. I first taught myself HTML when I was a teenager so I could modify my profile on xanga.com.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="text" data-aos="zoom-out"
    data-aos-anchor="#trigger-earth" id="third-text">
    <p>During university, I learned how to build websites with Flash. Then while working full-time, my employer at the time wanted to re-design their website. I took a class at General Assembly to learn front end web development. With those skills, I then built and deployed my first website. </p>
  </div>

  <div class="text" data-aos="zoom-out"
      data-aos-anchor="#first" id="fourth-text">
    <p>In summer of of 2017, I moved to London. After moving to London, I wanted to continue to learn more about the web, so I took a full-stack web development course at Le Wagon. At Le Wagon, I learned Ruby on Rails, JavaScript, AJAX, HTML, SCSS, PostgreSQL, Heroku, and more!</p>
  </div>
</div>







